---
title: Turkey Pasta E Fagioli Soup with Garlicky Breadsticks & Parsley
description: This soul-warming vegan soup is the culinary equivalent of a cozy blanket. It’s chock full of goodness, with earthy cannellini and kidney beans, tender onion and celery, and springy couscous in a savory tomato and mushroom broth. Throw in lots of fresh parsley, serve with a side of crisp garlic breadsticks, and you’ve got an ideal vegan dinner or lunch idea! Get ready to wrap yourself in this meal that’s as satisfying and comforting as it is delicious.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/665df043bb68d6ba93ee199b-91a11370.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/675a194fb3cc8de1f221d338-en-US.pdf
cuisine: Southern Europe
course: main course
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 930 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 103 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 1650 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/turkey-pasta-e-fagioli-soup-675a194fb3cc8de1f221d338
author: HelloFresh
time required: 35 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1} into 1⁄4-inch pieces. Halve @celery{2.5%ounce} lengthwise; dice into 1⁄4-inch pieces. Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1}. Drain and rinse @kidney beans{1}. Roughly chop @parsley{¼%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pot over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Transfer to a plate. Reserve pot.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add onion, celery, @Italian Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{} to taste. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are tender and lightly browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> If onion browns too quickly, add a splash of water and lower heat.

Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @mushroom stock concentrate{2}, @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce}, half the cannellini beans, half the kidney beans, @water{2%cups}, and a big pinch of salt and pepper.

> Use all the cannellini and kidney beans and 4 cups water for 4 servings.

Increase heat to medium high and bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until beans and couscous are tender, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Use pot used for sausage or turkey here. Once beans and couscous are tender, stir sausage or turkey into soup.

Meanwhile, halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise; slice each half lengthwise into thirds.

In a large #bowl, toss baguette pieces with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, remaining garlic powder, and salt and pepper to taste until evenly coated. Arrange seasoned baguette pieces on a #baking sheet{} and bake on top rack until lightly toasted, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove sheet from oven; carefully flip breadsticks and return to top rack until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Divide soup between #bowls{}; garnish with parsley. Serve with breadsticks on the side.